## Package Responsibility

This package is the most sensitive in the codebase. Every correctness property of the
system's restart-resilience depends on these two files being implemented exactly right.
Read this file more carefully than any other AGENTS.md in the repository.

---

## The Authoritative State Rule — One More Time

The dataset repo is the source of truth. The in-memory cache is a volatile read model.
These are not equivalent and they are not interchangeable. If you are writing a code
path where the cache is consulted to make a decision that affects a job's lifecycle
(whether to process it, whether to skip a chunk, whether to retry), you are making the
cache authoritative. That is a bug. The cache exists only so the UI can read job state
without hitting the Hub API every 5 seconds.

The test that distinguishes authoritative from non-authoritative: if the Space
restarts right now and the cache is empty, can the system reconstruct the correct
current state by reading from the Hub? If yes, the cache is a read model. If no,
something that should be in the Hub is only in the cache. Fix it.

